This well made spear was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
Another of history's most basic weapons, the spear is nevertheless a formidable weapon.  Little more than a simple shaft topped with a sharpened head, the spear is the staple of many a militia.
This well made rapier was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
The rapier is a light, thrusting sword popular among nobles and swashbucklers.  Often associated with dueling and sport fighting, rapiers are nonetheless deadly in trained hands.
This well made dagger was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
A basic but versatile weapon, the dagger consists of a double-edged piercing blade that typically ranges from about six to 24 inches in length.

This book was a somewhat famous writing by an Ilmatari Painbearer, but was so old that his or her name was no longer attributed to the methods contained therein.

In this tale, a child with scuffed knees cries out in pain. Hearing this, the Painbearer suggested the use of a simple herb often recommended for treating heat-illness: humble garlic. By treating bandages with this essential substance, one could accelerate the normal course of recovery from injury. Most consider it a staple tale of Ilmater's priests easing suffering for any and all.

Creating Bandages:
Add a Hand of Garlic and Rags items into your Crafter's Box, and use the Combiner on the Crafting Box. Your check will be modified by your healing skill and relevant backgrounds or proficiencies. Each attempt will cost 2 gold.

Use: Bandages can only be used on unarmored creatures who are not in combat.
